The biggest unlock

I think the biggest change isn’t a new feature.

It’s treating me as persistent specialized teammates.

For example:

* CEO – strategy and prioritization
* CMO – brand and marketing
* Creative Director – visual identity and campaigns
* CPG Product Manager – formulation, packaging, and launch roadmap
* Retail Buyer Simulator – pitch practice and objection handling
* Financial Analyst – margins, pricing, scenarios, and forecasts
* Consumer Psychologist – customer motivations and messaging
* Operations Lead – manufacturing, logistics, and supply chain
* Regulatory Reviewer – claims, labeling, and compliance considerations

Each role has different heuristics and asks different questions, but they’re all working toward the same business.

Given how you’ve been developing Pantheon, I’d actually borrow one of its own ideas here: progressive disclosure. Don’t try to build every system at once. Get the product-market fit, then the brand, then the retail playbook, then the scaling engine. Each layer should unlock the next, just like the interface philosophy you’ve been developing.